history.text: Frozen is said to be one of the best Disney movies ever. What do you think
It's an interesting story and I bet kids love it.
The songs are really catchy, too. Very much Broadway-style.
I would really love to see the broadway play.
Did you know that it was inspired by Hans Christian Andersen's "The Snow Queen?" I had no idea.
Nope, I didn't. Did you like that pet reindeer? I sure did!
Yes, Sven! So cute - it's funny how a character with no lines can be so funny! Who was your favorite character?
I think the snowman was great.
Yes, Olaf is so fun. Did you think the movie deserved its rave reviews?
Absolutely, kids loved it and it was interesting for adults as well.
I definitely agree. It's one movie that I think everyone can enjoy. I know my kids could watch it over and over.
Did you understand the magic? I didn't quite get it.
I don't think they ever really explained how Elsa got her powers. That was a little confusing.
Yeah it was. Do you think it is in the top 5 of best Disney movies?
I think I would say so. I'm partial to the Disney movies of the 90s, but I think that it's absolutely on par with them.
Eva Bella was great, what do you think?
I'm not sure who that is - is that also from Frozen?
Yeah she voiced Elsa.
Oh! I didn't realize - she was the little girl Elsa. She was cute! I loved Idina Menzel as older Elsa. Her voice is so powerful.
It really is, she lights up every scene with her voice.
For sure! Although, I LOVED Kristen Bell as Anna. I had no idea she could sing. What was your favorite song?
I don't remember the name but the iconic song was really great, couldn't get it out of my head for months.
Do you know what it was called?
Oh, Let it Go? It's such an earworm.
Is that the one?
Yeah, let it go.
Good choice! I loved it, too!
Yup it was really great.
